name: Set of four vintage Tulip chairs - Eero Saarinen for Knoll

condition.details: Wear consistent with age and use.

specifications.rawSpecificationsHTML: A stunning set of four vintage Tulip chairs, attributed to Eero Saarinen for Knoll. These iconic chairs, renowned for their elegant organic shape and minimalist pedestal base, are true mid-century design classics. The chairs feature an off-white plastic shell seat on a white-coated metal pedestal base, with removable natural/beige fabric cushions. The chairs are attributed to Knoll due to their design, weight, and craftsmanship. Remnants of silver stickers on the seat, a label type used by Knoll in the 1960s/'70s, suggest possible original labeling. The set is in vintage condition, with characteristic signs of use consistent with its age, without compromising design or functionality. A timeless design, perfect for both modern and retro interiors! Dimensions: Height: ± 81 cm Seat height: ± 46 cm Width: ± 49 cm Depth: ± 53 cm Price for the set of four
